==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|absteynen|lang=enm}}, {{term|abstenen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|astenir|lang=fro}}, {{term|abstenir|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|abstinere|lang=la}}, {{term|abstentum||keep or refrain from|lang=la}}; from prefix {{term|abs-|from|lang=la}} + {{term|tenere|hold|lang=la}}. See [[tenable]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əbˈsteɪn/}}
* {{rhymes|eɪn}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{intransitive}} [[refrain|Refrain]] from (something); hold one's self [[aloof]]; to [[forbear]] or keep from doing, especially an [[indulgence]] of the passions or appetites; -- with ''from''.
# {{intransitive}} To [[shun]] voluntarily.
#:* Not a few '''abstained''' from voting. - [[w:Thomas Babington Macaulay|Thomas Babington Macaulay]]
#:* Who '''abstains''' from meat that is not gaunt? - Shakespeare, ''Richard II, II-i''
# {{intransitive}} Deliberately refrain from casting one's [[vote]] at a meeting where one is present.
# {{transitive}} [[hinder|Hinder]]; [[withhold]].
#:* Whether he '''abstain''' men from marrying. - [[w:John Milton|John Milton]]

